item.name: 221B Baker Street: The Master Detective Game
Another Day, Another Dollar: Kung Fu
Cannibal Pygmies in the Jungle of Doom
Catacombs
item.comment: Adorable. Does exactly what it claims to do, without too much baggage. Begs for expansions, and I desperately hope it sells enough to get them.

item.name: Cluzzle
item.comment: Quite good. Generally better than Barbarossa. ( I feel like a traitor for saying that.) There are some grey areas around guessing as spelled out in Mike's review that keep this from a 10.

item.name: Cows Can't Dance (but they like to be asked)
Dia de los Muertos
item.comment: Ok. 4 years after finishing development and 100 or so plays, I still really love playing this stupid game. Although I feel just a wee bit guilty about begging people to play it. Sad, really.

item.name: Doctor Who: Battle for the Universe
Go to the Head of the Class
Der Herr der Ringe: Die Zwei Türme – das Kartenspiel
James Ernest's Totally Renamed Spy Game
Nightmare House
item.comment: 8 pages of the densest and nastiest rules I've ever faced. Interesting ideas but nearly unplayable in practice.

item.name: Star Saga: One – Beyond The Boundary
item.comment: This is one of my favorite games. I've played both twice, and am happily waiting another 6 years so I can have forgotten enough to play again.

item.name: Star Saga: Two – The Clathran Menace
item.comment: The story is not as compelling as the first, but it makes up in weird events and a better game system.

item.name: Supremacy: Neutron Bombs and Killer Satellites
The Wreck of the B.S.M. Pandora
